.TH "RTCINBOUNDRTPSTREAMSTATS.FRAMEWIDTH" "3JS" "August 15, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
RTCInboundRtpStreamStats.frameWidth \- RTCInboundRtpStreamStats:
frameWidth property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]frameWidth\f[B]\f[R] property of the
\f[CR]RTCInboundRtpStreamStats\f[R] dictionary indicates the width of
the last decoded frame, in pixels.
.PP
Note that the resolution of the encoded frame may be lower than that of
the media source, which is provided in
\f[CR]RTCVideoSourceStats.width\f[R].
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] The value is undefined for audio streams, or before the
first frame is encoded.
.RE
.SH VALUE
A positive integer, in pixels.
